Class EstablishedEventPrivateData

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • com.avaya.csta.binding.EstablishedEventPrivateData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class EstablishedEventPrivateData
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Avaya extensions to EstablishedEvent.
    EstablishedEventPrivateData Parameters
    trunkGroup String Specifies the trunk group number from which the call originated.
    trunkMember String Specifies the trunk member number from which the call originated.
    acdGroup DeviceID Specifies the ACD split extension to which the call is established.
    lookAheadInfo LookAheadInfo Specifies the lookahead interflow information received from the established call.
    userEnteredCode UserEnteredCode Specifies the code/digits that may have been entered by the caller through the call prompting feature or the collected digits feature.
    reason ReasonCode Specifies the reason that caused this event. The supported values are:
    • none
    • answerNormal
    • answerTimed
    • answerVoiceEnergy
    • answerMachineDetected
    • reorder
    • noCircuit
    • intercept
    • unassignedNumber
    • invalidNumber
    • unspecified
    distributingDevice SubjectDeviceID Specifies the original distributing device of the call before the call is conferenced.
    distributingVDN SubjectDeviceID The VDN extension associated with the distributing device. The field gets set under the following conditions.
    • When the application monitors the VDN in question and sees the DeliveredEvent.
    • When the application monitors an agent and receives a call that came from that monitored VDN (that is, in the Delivered, Established, Transferred, and Conferenced events).
    originalCallInfo OriginalCallInfo Specifies the original call information for the EstablishedEvent:
    • reason
    • lookaheadInfo
    • userEnteredCode
    • userData
    • callLinkageData
    • deviceHistory
    Version:
    $Revision$ $Date$

      • getOriginalCallInfo

        public OriginalCallInfo getOriginalCallInfo()
        Returns the value of field 'originalCallInfo'. The field 'originalCallInfo' has the following description: Specifies the Original Call Information.

        Note that information is not repeated in the originalCallInfo, if it is already reported in the CSTA service parameters or in the private data. For example, if the userEnteredCode in the private data is the original userEnteredCode, the userEnteredCode in the originalCallInfo will be null. Only when new userEnteredCode is received and reported in the userEnteredCode, the originalCallInfo will have the original userEnteredCode.

        Note: For the Delivered Event sent to the initiatedCall of a Consultation Call, the originalCallInfo is taken from the existingCall specified in the Consultation Call request. Thus the application can pass the original call information between two calls. The consultedDevice of the Consultation Call must reside on the same switch and must be monitored by the same AE Services.

        The original call information contains the following fields for the EstablishedEvent:

        • reason
        • lookaheadInfo
        • userEnteredCode
        • userData
        • callLinkageData
        • deviceHistory
        Returns:
        OriginalCallInfo
